<eesti>Lisa 2 </eesti>
<inglise>Annex 2 </inglise>
<eesti>teede- ja sideministri 6. detsembri 2000. a m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 106 juurde </eesti>
<inglise>to Regulation No. 106 of the Minister of Transport and Communications of 6 December 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>A- ja B-kategooria keskkonnaohtlikud kemikaalid, mida paragrahvi 18 l&otilde;ike 5 punkt 2 ei luba merel laadida </eesti>
<inglise>Category A and B environmentally hazardous chemicals which are not permitted to be loaded at sea pursuant to clause 18 (5) 2) </inglise>
<eesti>* M&auml;rkus. </eesti>
<inglise>* Note. </inglise>
<eesti>A-kategooria aine on bioakumuleeruv ja ohtlik mere elustikule v&otilde;i inimese tervisele; LC50 (kontsentratsioon vees, mille juures pooled katsealustest hukkuvad) on alla 1 mg/kg v&otilde;i LC50 on vahemikus 1 kuni 10 mg/kg, kuid kaasnevad muud ohud mere elustikule. </eesti>
<inglise>Category A substances are bioaccumulated and liable to produce a hazard to marine biota or human health; LC50 (concentration in water at which one-half of the test subjects perish) is less than 1 mg/kg, or LC50 is between 1 and 10 mg/kg, but other hazards to marine biota are involved. Category B substances are bioaccumulated with a short retention (up to one week); produce tainting of marine organisms used for food; LC50 is between 1 and 10 mg/kg or LC50 is between 10 and 100 mg/kg, but other hazards to marine biota are involved. </inglise>

